		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Nov 17th 10:24 AM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1100702458572234587&num=7&post=1&replyto=1100705089574439010"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1100705089574439010></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id=Scholar>Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="73" width="100" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/Avatar2.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1475 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>It's just you. It's completely the opposite. Whenever you have a bard in your group, there's not much need for a chanter... Actually, I love having a chanter in my group. For one, it takes the pressure of slowing/CC off of me. I don't have any problem doing it, but it slows me down a lot. I can pull quickly and efficiently if that's all I have to worry about (save preslows and emergency CC). If I'm pulling, CC, slows, haste... it's exciting, but it gets annoying after awhile. Especially when you get heavy resists. That's when you start to hate the recast time on RoT. It annoys me to no avail that I have to have a normal duration slow up just in case my RoT gets resisted.<br><br>It's possible that you're not seeing as many bards in the lower levels. There are a lot of factors that come into play (ie new games coming out that people want to try). The removal of AE kiting may have a contribution to that... but my stance stays the same on that. If someone started a bard just so they could AE their way to 50+ in a week, it's better that they never started a bard in the first place.<br><br>Now, you say you never search for them, but you never see them... I can understand that. I never search for wizards, and I very very rarely see them. It doesn't mean their not out there, it just means I don't notice.<br><br>A bards contributions to a group far outweigh their contributions to a raid (in most circumstances). We have 2 AE song lines. Our mana/regen and resists. Both are nice to have on a raid, yes, but the mana/regen rate is mostly useful for LONG raids, where a 15m/tick increase will actually add up. The resists are also nice, but more and more raid targets are designed with the bard in mind. Their AEs will have HUGE -resist modifiers so that even with a bard on the raid, you're more then likely going to get hit.<br><br>A well-played group bard though can do some amazing things. They can easily single-handedly wipe a group, or save a group even when things look completely out of hand. This can be said of many classes of course, but I do have a bit of a bias <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/wink.gif" />. One quick example. In BoT about 2 weeks ago, in middle sands, we attack Thorolf Sutherland. Something goes wrong and tank goes down. As the ranger is offtanking, I mem Song of Highsun real quick. When the ranger went down and I was the only melee left, I ran him up towards US a bit so the others could gate/zone out and then I highsunned him and faded. What could've easily been a complete wipe ended up with 2 dead, easily rezzed, and a second successful go at our named.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Monk</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td></tr></table>
