		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id=Scholar>Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="73" width="100" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/Avatar2.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1475 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I can only tell you my experiences. My bard is 64 with 35 AA atm.<br><br>DPS: Yes, bard DPS sucks. But there are ways around that. My bard just got a Dedrex's (sp) Flintforged Cudgel. It's become pretty popular for bards to utilize heavy hitting procs to increase their DPS. Our double attack sucks (and you have to buy an AA to get it), but with the purchase of a few key AA's (specifically Weapon Affinity 5, increases procs by 50% and Spell casting Fury 3, increases DD spell crits by 7% and 100% damage) a 625 proc that normally goes off twice a minute becomes a 625 proc that goes off 5-6 times a minute with a 7% chance of hitting for over 1200. That's a HEAVY hitter. Now, I know you're going to ask about aggro problems. Well, bard songs are hardcoded to generate very little aggro. Otherwise, we'd go splat all the time. We buff/heal 6 people every 3 seconds. Imagine the aggro that would generate if we generated normal spell aggro like other casters, not to mention our added aggro from melee. Now, here's some good news. MOST weapon procs fall under our spell coding when we use them. Just like we can use clickies and gate potions while running, because they fall under bard song coding when used by a bard. Last night, I proced 625 TWICE right off the bat on a pull. The cleric got aggro for hitting me with a HoT...<br><br>Another aspect to bard DPS is what we add to the GROUP. I know some people don't think of it that way, but it is a valid argument when comparing a chanter to a bard. A single bard isn't huge DPS. But think about what I add to the group... I normally twist (with epic in secondary) Marr (38 HP/20 mana per tick), PoV (all resists +~130/21 DS/10 AC), Rizlona's (+15% DD spell damage for group/+30% melee overhaste), and Warsong of Zek (60% haste, 71 Str, 33 Atk, 30 DS). So if you think about it, that's really adding a lot to the capabilities of the group. 51 DS from the bard that stacks with druids. The HP/Mana, the spell focus, the added STR/ATK and the overhaste. <br><br>Mezzing and slows: My slow is 52% and lasts a minute at NO mana costs. Better then any beast slow until they hit 65, then they get 65%. Yes, a chanter has bigger slows, can haste, and can mez and charm. Well, you know what? The chanter in my groups very rarely even need to do that. I more often then not pull singles, and if I pull doubles, I mez one on inc to split them easier, and I can melee, twist 3 songs and keep one mob mezzed without breaking a sweat. For hastes, a chanter will give the group 70% haste. Add that to the worn hastes and you're at the 100% cap. My WoZ and Riz's give 90% and allow everyone to go up to 130% haste. Who's haste is better? It's true that I don't spend every second in camp, but my songs last 18 seconds. I'm rarely gone for that long.<br><br>As far as pulling, monks are very capable pullers and rangers are very good outside. I would feel bad for the monk getting beat on so bad in most of the Omens zones where the mobs run at just under Selos speed, but they're very good everywhere else. I'd rather have a monk pull in a high resist situation myself.<br><br>What you have to remember is that you're comparing the normal capabilities of ONE class against the SPECIALTY capabilities of SEVERAL OTHER CLASSES. Of course those other classes are going to be better at <i>their</i> thing, but that bard can do it all relatively well.<br><br>If you are wanting a bard to bot for slows/haste/cc, yeah, you got the wrong class. But as a played character, a bard can be a huge addition to a group.<br> <br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Nov 18 11:17:36 2004 by Jiggidyjay</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Monk</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td></tr></table>
